#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.31:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 4. Sīsapāvanavagga → siṃsapāvanavaggo (bj, pts1) | sīsapāpaṇṇavaggo (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn56.31:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga "
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 31. Sīsapāvanasutta → siṃsapāsuttaṃ (bj) | siṃsapā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Sīsapāvanasutta "
msgstr "31. In a Rosewood Forest "

# NOTE: The simsapa is identified with Dalbergia sissoo, known as “North Indian Rosewood”. Since they’re in north India, I think just plain “rosewood” will do fine.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.438, sc1
#. VAR: sīsapāvane → siṃsapāvane (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.31:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati sīsapāvane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambī in a rosewood forest. "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā parittāni sīsapāpaṇṇāni pāṇinā gahetvā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha picked up a few rosewood leaves in his hand and addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.3"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.4"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "Which is more: "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.5"
msgid "yāni vā mayā parittāni sīsapāpaṇṇāni pāṇinā gahitāni yadidaṃ upari sīsapāvane”ti? "
msgstr "the few leaves in my hand, or those in the forest above me?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.31:1.6"
msgid "“Appamattakāni, bhante, bhagavatā parittāni sīsapāpaṇṇāni pāṇinā gahitāni; "
msgstr "“Sir, the few leaves in your hand are a tiny amount. "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.7"
msgid "atha kho etāneva bahutarāni yadidaṃ upari sīsapāvane”ti. "
msgstr "There are far more leaves in the forest above.” "

# NOTE: Following PTS, and apparently all manuscripts except the Burmese, which have appamattakam akkhatam
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.31:1.8"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, etadeva bahutaraṃ yaṃ vo mayā abhiññāya anakkhātaṃ. "
msgstr "“In the same way, there is much more that I have directly known but have not explained to you. What I have explained is a tiny amount. "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.9"
msgid "Kasmā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā anakkhātaṃ? "
msgstr "And why haven’t I explained it? "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.10"
msgid "Na hetaṃ, bhikkhave, atthasaṃhitaṃ nādibrahmacariyakaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "Because it’s not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

msgctxt "sn56.31:1.11"
msgid "tasmā taṃ mayā anakkhātaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s why I haven’t explained it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn56.31:2.1"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, mayā akkhātaṃ? "
msgstr "And what have I explained? "

msgctxt "sn56.31:2.2"
msgid "‘Idaṃ dukkhan’ti, bhikkhave, mayā akkhātaṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti mayā akkhātaṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti mayā akkhātaṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti mayā akkhātaṃ. "
msgstr "I have explained: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.31:3.1"
msgid "Kasmā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā akkhātaṃ? "
msgstr "And why have I explained this? "

msgctxt "sn56.31:3.2"
msgid "Etañhi, bhikkhave, atthasaṃhitaṃ etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ etaṃ nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "Because it’s beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. It leads to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

msgctxt "sn56.31:3.3"
msgid "tasmā taṃ mayā akkhātaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s why I’ve explained it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn56.31:4.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.31:4.2"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

